==English==

===Etymology===
Alternate form of [[bing]], suggesting a ringing sound (1925).

===Noun===
{{en-noun-unc}}

# A [[game of chance]] for two or more playes, who mark off numbers on a grid as they are called out by another person (the ''[[caller]]''); the game is won by the first person to call out "bingo!" or "house!" on crossing off all numbers on the grid or in one line of the grid.
# A fictional dog owned by a farmer in a children's song.

====Synonyms====
*[[housey-housey]], [[lotto]]

